    # =======================================================================
    # SETUP GUIDE — Required secrets & configuration
    # =======================================================================
    #
    # This workflow requires several GitHub Actions secrets to be configured
    # in your repository (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New
    # repository secret).
    #
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # JIRA SECRETS  (required for all modes)
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    #
    # JIRA_BASE_URL
    #   Your Atlassian instance base URL — no trailing slash.
    #   Example: https://your-org.atlassian.net
    #
    # JIRA_USER
    #   The email address of the Atlassian account used for API calls.
    #   Example: ci-bot@your-org.com
    #
    # JIRA_TOKEN
    #   An Atlassian API token for the account above.
    #   Generate one at: https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
    #   ⚠️  This is NOT your Atlassian password — you must create a dedicated
    #       API token. Tokens can be scoped to read-only if desired.
    #
    # How to verify JIRA credentials locally:
    #   curl -u "you@org.com:YOUR_TOKEN" \
    #        "https://your-org.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/myself" \
    #        -H "Accept: application/json"
    #   A 200 response with your account info means credentials are correct.
    #
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # BRANCH NAMING CONVENTION
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    #
    # The workflow extracts the JIRA ticket key from the PR branch name.
    # Your branch must contain a key matching [A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]+, e.g.:
    #
    #   SCRUM-42-add-login-page       ✅  detected as SCRUM-42
    #   feature/PROJ-7-refactor-auth  ✅  detected as PROJ-7
    #   NOJIRA-cleanup-readme         ⏭️  explicitly skipped
    #   fix-typo                      ⚠️  no key found, JIRA steps skipped
    #
    # This is a test, hellow to CAS team. TEST
{% if options.mode in ('anthropic', 'anthropic-agentic') %}
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # ANTHROPIC SECRETS  (required for mode: {{ options.mode }})
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    #
    # ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
    #   Your Anthropic API key — used to call the Claude API for code review.
    #   Generate one at: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
    #   ⚠️  Ensure your Anthropic account has API access enabled and
    #       sufficient credits/quota for the model: {{ options.model }}.
    #
    # Model configured: {{ options.model }}
    #   Adjust options.model in workflows.yaml to change the Claude model.
    #   See available models: https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/about-claude/models
    #
{% endif %}
{% if options.mode == 'copilot' %}
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # COPILOT REVIEWER  (required for mode: copilot)
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    #
    # No additional secrets are needed — this mode uses the built-in
    # GITHUB_TOKEN and requests 'copilot-pull-request-reviewer' as a reviewer.
    #
    # Requirements:
    #   • Your GitHub plan must include Copilot code review (GitHub Copilot
    #     Enterprise or a compatible Copilot Business plan).
    #   • The Copilot reviewer feature must be enabled for your organization:
    #     Org Settings → Copilot → Policies → "Enable Copilot pull request
    #     review suggestions"
    #   • The repository must have Copilot enabled.
    #   See: https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/using-github-copilot/code-review
    #
    # ⚠️  Common error: "Reviews may only be requested from collaborators"
    #   This means 'copilot-pull-request-reviewer' is not recognized in your
    #   repository. This happens when:
    #     - Your GitHub plan does not include Copilot Enterprise or a
    #       Copilot Business plan with code review enabled.
    #     - The repository is personal (not under an organization), and
    #       GitHub Copilot code review is not available for personal repos.
    #     - The feature has not been enabled at the org level (see above).
    #   The workflow handles this gracefully — a warning is logged and the
    #   job continues. No action is required unless you intend to use Copilot
    #   code review; in that case, verify your plan and org settings.
    #
{% endif %}
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    # SUMMARY OF SECRETS FOR THIS WORKFLOW  (mode: {{ options.mode }})
    # -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    #
    # Secret name         Required   Description
    # ------------------  ---------  ----------------------------------------
    # JIRA_BASE_URL       ✅ yes     Atlassian instance URL
    # JIRA_USER           ✅ yes     Atlassian account email
    # JIRA_TOKEN          ✅ yes     Atlassian API token
{% if options.mode in ('anthropic', 'anthropic-agentic') %}
    # ANTHROPIC_API_KEY   ✅ yes     Anthropic API key (Claude)
{% else %}
    # ANTHROPIC_API_KEY   ➖ n/a     Not used in {{ options.mode }} mode
{% endif %}
    # GITHUB_TOKEN        ✅ auto    Provided automatically by GitHub Actions
    #
    # Missing secrets cause steps to be skipped gracefully with a warning
    # rather than failing the workflow with an error.
    #
    # =======================================================================
